class Solution {
    public boolean detectCapitalUse(String word) {
        int count = 0;
        for (char c : word.toCharArray()) {
            if (Character.isUpperCase(c)) {
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count == 0 || count == word.length() || (count == 1 && Character.isUpperCase(word.charAt(0)));
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the word once, counting the number of uppercase letters. It then checks if the count is 0 (all lowercase), equal to the word length (all uppercase), or 1 and the first letter is uppercase. This approach is efficient as it only requires a single pass through the string.
